history.content:
1. Common choices: CS 170, 188, 160, 169

2. It varies, but CS 170, 188 are again common. In this limbo period, we recommend students sign up for CS 61c/ee16a/tech elective instead

3. Your peers probably have more insight, but we often hear that it can be as busy as some of the CS upper divs.

4. 170 material is applicable in a variety of areas in CS, and especially in the remaining 170 series: 172, 174, 176

children.subject:
> Is CS 61C more or less challenging/time-consuming compared to some CS upper divs?

It depends. 186 < 188 < 61C < 170 < 189 for me, in terms of workload.

history.content:
I took CS 61A last semester and I an currently taking CS 70. I plan to take CS 61BL during summer.

1. What upper divs are generally recommended immediately after CS 61A, 61B and 70 (also MATH 53 & 54)?

2. Since I will still be undeclared during course registration period, what are some upper divs that are possible for undeclared students to get in?

3. Is CS 61C more or less challenging/time-consuming compared to some CS upper divs?

4. Will the algorithms taught in CS 170 be used in other CS upper divs?

Thx so much!
